The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for computer-assisted synthesis planning, which is a problem in chemical engineering. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a Markov decision process, which is a common technique in Control Engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of identifying reaction sites in molecules, which suggests that it may also belong to the Scientific Computing (cs.SD) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories, which often deal with problems involving complex data structures.
